\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3360220 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9575233\charrsid7744433 In the district who would be considered to be the most important people?

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12744824 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9575233\charrsid7744433 Well I don't know. I 
suppose the headmaster and headmistress, they both lived near. I don't know that there was anybody considered to be - special really. We'd doctors and all sorts round us you know. I don't think anybody would be really. Then of course there were all the bi
g houses you know on the other side, just above us, from - from Albet Road going up you know there were all those big houses I suppose - some people would consider that but - I don't think we ever thought about it really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3360220 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9575233\charrsid7744433 What about the small shopkeepers, who did they associate with?
