I suppose more or less their own neihbours you see. 'Cos a lot of them had shops in what they used to call their front parlour, you know, just - that's a - of course we being just wholesale those were the people we - 
served a lot you see and - they were a very nice lot of people. Very nice. I've always been very fond of that type of person. Had a lot to do with them really in working at the Girls Club too you know, the working girls, they were all mill girls when we f
irst started there of course - it was what it was started for, to help them that - they were a nice lot. I was very fond of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3360220 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9575233\charrsid7744433 What sort of things did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12744824 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9575233\charrsid7744433 
Well - I used to have - one time I had a sewing class. See, they used to get bits of
 material from their mills and they used to say, can you teach us to make a - an underskirt, can you teach us - we never went in anything that we didn't want them to copy because they used to say, I'd like a blouse like that. And you couldn't do it. But o
f course the ready made age took that over you see. But - I was very fond of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3360220 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9575233\charrsid7744433 Did you mix with them at all outside the girls club?
